{"id":2980,"date":"2018-09-19T14:23:46","date_gmt":"2018-09-19T13:23:46","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.robinmcdonald.co.uk\/?p=2980"},"modified":"2018-09-19T14:23:46","modified_gmt":"2018-09-19T13:23:46","slug":"new-drivers-biggest-danger-on-the-road-driver-distraction","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.robinmcdonald.co.uk\/2018\/09\/19\/new-drivers-biggest-danger-on-the-road-driver-distraction\/","title":{"rendered":"NEW DRIVERS! Biggest Danger on the road? Driver Distraction&#8230;.."},"content":{"rendered":"<p>So you are new to driving?&#8230;at Aplus Driving Academy we want you to be safe and enjoy your newly acquired skills. We all know these days we have to be adaptable and multitasking is at the forefront of how we are today. However, this does not apply to your attention span in a vehicle&#8230;.. Here are a few things you need to remember:<\/p>\n<p>Distractions:<\/p>\n<div class=\"post-area col  span_9\">\n<article id=\"post-436\" class=\"regular post-436 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail category-stay-safe\">\n<div class=\"inner-wrap animated\">\n<div class=\"post-content\">\n<div class=\"content-inner\">\n<div id=\"fws_5ba24a44d503e\" class=\"wpb_row vc_row-fluid vc_row standard_section   \" data-midnight=\"dark\" data-bg-mobile-hidden=\"\">\n<div class=\"col span_12 dark left\">\n<div class=\"vc_col-sm-12 wpb_column column_container vc_column_container col no-extra-padding instance-1\" data-border-radius=\"none\" data-shadow=\"none\" data-border-animation=\"\" data-border-animation-delay=\"\" data-border-width=\"none\" data-border-style=\"solid\" data-border-color=\"\" data-bg-cover=\"\" data-padding-pos=\"all\" data-has-bg-color=\"false\" data-bg-color=\"\" data-bg-opacity=\"1\" data-hover-bg=\"\" data-hover-bg-opacity=\"1\" data-animation=\"\" data-delay=\"0\">\n<div class=\"vc_column-inner\">\n<div class=\"wpb_wrapper\">\n<div class=\"wpb_text_column wpb_content_element \">\n<div class=\"wpb_wrapper\">\n<ul>\n<li>Texting \u2013 51%<\/li>\n<li>Children in the car \u2013 36%<\/li>\n<li>Talking on the Phone \u2013 45%<\/li>\n<li>Chatting to a passenger \u2013 32.3%<\/li>\n<li>Changing radio\/CD\/MP3 \u2013 40.4%<\/li>\n<li>Road Rage \u2013 32%<\/li>\n<li>Staring at an accident \u2013 39.8%<\/li>\n<li>Having an argument \u2013 31%<\/li>\n<li>Eating or Drinking \u2013 37%<\/li>\n<li>Lighting a cigarette \u2013 29%<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Dealing with distractions:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>If you need to do something distracting, find a safe place to pull over<\/li>\n<li>Recognise what makes you distracted, then work out whether or not you really need to do it<\/li>\n<li>Make sure you\u2019re ready to drive before setting off. After an emotional event, you might need to take some time to calm down<\/li>\n<li>Use technology sensibly \u2013 or not at all<\/li>\n<li>Plan your route in advance so you\u2019re not having to work out your route as you go along.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>These simple steps can and do avoid collisions.<\/p>\n<p><strong>How frustrating are all these things? We all see examples of this every day&#8230;.let&#8217;s just not be one of them.\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"at-below-post addthis_tool\" data-url=\"http:\/\/www.newdriverni.com\/most-common-distractions\/\" data-title=\"Most Common Distractions\">\n<div id=\"atstbx\" class=\"at-resp-share-element at-style-responsive addthis-smartlayers addthis-animated at4-show\" role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"at-be47b930-8369-4c96-b381-cb463823ee29\"><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/article>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"sidebar\" class=\"col span_3 col_last\" data-nectar-ss=\"1\">\n<div class=\"theiaStickySidebar\">\n<div id=\"nectar_popular_posts-2\" class=\"widget nectar_popular_posts_widget\"><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>So you are new to driving?&#8230;at Aplus Driving Academy we want you to be sa